Citation.sAbstract: Molar excess enthalpies ( ) at 298.15 K and 308.15 K and molar excess volumes ( ) at 308.15  K for formamide (1) + 1-propanol or 2-propanol (2) mixtures have been measured over the entire  composition range. The excess enthalpies and excess volumes data have been utilized to study the  thermodynamics of molecular interactions in terms of Prigogine-Flory-Patterson theory and  Treszczanowicz-Benson association model with a Flory contribution term. In this paper, this  Treszczanowicz-Benson association model was applied, for the first time, to binary mixtures  containing both components associated (propanol and formamide) through hydrogen bonding. In both  the cases, when either of formamide or propanol was assumed to be associated, the calculated and  values compared well with corresponding experimental data. Extent of inter-molecular H-bonding in  formamide and propanols in their binary mixtures was also reflected in their molar enthalpy of  association of H-bonding and association constant .
Citation.sTitle: Molar excess enthalpies and molar excess volumes of formamide + 1-propanol or 2-propanol and  thermodynamic modeling by Prigogine-Flory-Patterson theory and Treszczanowicz-Benson  association model
